Port-Harcourt-based fashion designer Princewill Obinna Iwueke also known as Willz Obinna has spoken about his passion for giving and philanthropy. According to him, the older he gets, the more he realises how giving and showing love to other people has brought about good tidings in his life and building his brand “I learnt giving and donating while growing up with my parents. Although individual giveaways or family giveaways don’t mean you are too rich or something, it’s just a passion I developed from my parents from the memories we spent together,” he said.   Yoruba actor, Tafa Oloyede, for burial Feb. 11     Erigga: No girl should be given Valentine’s gift…     96 per cent of Nigerian men want me badly – Bobrisky   Continuing, he added: “Growing up, my mother would have a big Christmas tree, Christmas lights and presents under the tree to celebrate how far we have come over the years. - Advertisement - “This usually happens every year in our family and also the giving out to loved ones and to the less privileged out there. “Giving has brought happiness and good payback to me and family, and also happiness to people out there which I see as a good thing.” The designer and curator hails from Imo State but is based in Port Harcourt, Rivers State